{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38f22b38-dc76-4749-be39-89e4d9a39960","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n}\n```\n\n**Why?**\n\n- **`[ExpectedException]`** passes if *any* line throws — masking bugs (e.g., the constructor throwing instead of `CreateUser`).\n- **`Assert.ThrowsException`** scopes the assertion to the exact call, and lets you inspect the exception:\n\n```csharp\nvar ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n    () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\nAssert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"21ebedb2-c3ab-44fc-99be-7538c7b960aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no need to explore a codebase.","outputTokens":277,"requestId":"3410:1BE42F:CC64DD:EDCC1F:69F40273"},"id":"1f103746-7026-4e4f-9bbd-53a2cb123bec","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:31:37.952Z","parentId":"ad663e23-da79-4a85-8d9f-fdbf1a9d8976"}
